'''Oudenhoorn''' ({{coor dm|51|50|N|4|12|E|type:city(584)}}) is a town in the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] province of [[South Holland]]. It is a part of the municipality of [[Bernisse]], and lies about 3 km east of [[Hellevoetsluis]].

In 2001, the town of Oudenhoorn had 584 inhabitants. The built-up area of the town was 0.11 km<sup>2</sup>, and contained 247 residences.<ref name="CBS">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), ''Bevolkingskernen in Nederland 2001'' [http://www.cbs.nl/nl-NL/menu/themas/milieu-natuur-ruimte/ruimte/publicaties/cartografie-geografie/geografische-data/2001-bevolkingskernen-in-nederland.htm]. Statistics are for the continuous built-up area.</ref> The wider statistical area of Oudenhoorn has a population of around 1210.<ref name="CBS2">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), ''Gemeente Op Maat 2004: Bernisse'' [http://www.cbs.nl/nl-NL/menu/themas/nederland-regionaal/nederland-regionaal/publicaties/gemeente-op-maat/2004/alfabet/b/2004-bernisse.htm].</ref>

